

     
      One of the most popular design patterns is the Data Access Object (DAO) pattern. It's used when you want to separate your presentation code from the code that accesses the back-end containing your data. The back-end is typically a database, but it could be anything: a flat file on your hard disk, a message queue connecting to a mainframe, or a web service interface to some server.   This article from Java Boutique will walk you through DAO and using it in Apache Struts.  [Resource-Type: Article; Category: Java/J2EE; Level: ADV; XRating: 3.5]
     
    
